The values that can be written are: deleteAllInBound(2)...delete all in-bound filter lists from all ports. deleteAllOutBound(3)..delete all out-bound filter lists from all ports. addAllInBound(4)......add all in-bound filter lists to all ports. addAllOutBound(5).....add all out-bound filter lists to all ports. snDvmrpEnable.name: snDvmrpEnable
snDvmrpEnable.description: Enable or disable DVMRP on this router.

snDvmrpGenerationId.name: snDvmrpGenerationId
snDvmrpGenerationId.description: The generation identifier for the routing process. This is used by neighboring routers to detect whether pruning information should be resent.

snDvmrpProbeInterval.name: snDvmrpProbeInterval
snDvmrpProbeInterval.description: This is the time interval at which the router sends out probe messages to discover neighbour routers. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpReportInterval.name: snDvmrpReportInterval
snDvmrpReportInterval.description: This is the time interval at which the router sends out full report messages. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpTriggerInterval.name: snDvmrpTriggerInterval
snDvmrpTriggerInterval.description: This is the time interval at which triggered updates are sent out. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpNeighborRouterTimeout.name: snDvmrpNeighborRouterTimeout
snDvmrpNeighborRouterTimeout.description: This is the time interval after which the neighbour router is considered down. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpRouteExpireTime.name: snDvmrpRouteExpireTime
snDvmrpRouteExpireTime.description: This is the time interval after which the route expires and becomes unreachable. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpRouteDiscardTime.name: snDvmrpRouteDiscardTime
snDvmrpRouteDiscardTime.description: This is the time interval after which a route is discarded from the route table. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpPruneAge.name: snDvmrpPruneAge
snDvmrpPruneAge.description: This is the duration of time for which the prune state is stored. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpGraftRetransmitTime.name: snDvmrpGraftRetransmitTime
snDvmrpGraftRetransmitTime.description: This is the time interval after which a graft message will be retransmitted if graft acknowledge message has not been received. Value is in number of seconds. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpDefaultRoute.name: snDvmrpDefaultRoute
snDvmrpDefaultRoute.description: This is the IP address of a router that is connected to one of the directly attached subnet. If a multicast route is not present on the local router, this default route will be used for multicast forwarding. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this object is writen.

snDvmrpVInterfaceTable.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceTable
snDvmrpVInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's DVMRP virtual interfaces. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this table is read or writen.

snDvmrpVInterfaceEntry.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceEntry
snDvmrpVInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the snDvmrpVInterfaceTable. This row augments ipMRouteInterfaceEntry in the IP Multicast MIB, where the threshold object resides.

snDvmrpVInterfaceVifIndex.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceVifIndex
snDvmrpVInterfaceVifIndex.description: The ifIndex value of this DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVInterfaceType.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceType
snDvmrpVInterfaceType.description: The type of this DVMRP virtual interface, whether it uses a tunnel, a physical interface for which we are a querier, or a physical interface for which we are not a querier. For write operation, this object can only accept tunnel(1) to configure a tunnel interface or subnet(3) to configure a physical interface.

snDvmrpVInterfaceOperState.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceOperState
snDvmrpVInterfaceOperState.description: The current operational state of this DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVInterfaceLocalAddress.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceLocalAddress
snDvmrpVInterfaceLocalAddress.description: The IP address of the local end of this DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVInterfaceRemoteAddress.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceRemoteAddress
snDvmrpVInterfaceRemoteAddress.description: The IP address of the remote end of this DVMRP virtual interface. For a tunnel, this is the IP address of the neighboring router. For a subnet, this is the subnet address.

snDvmrpVInterfaceRemoteSubnetMask.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceRemoteSubnetMask
snDvmrpVInterfaceRemoteSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for a directly connected subnet. For a tunnel, this should be 0.0.0.0.

snDvmrpVInterfaceMetric.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceMetric
snDvmrpVInterfaceMetric.description: The distance metric for this DVMRP virtual interface which is used to calculate distance vectors.

snDvmrpVInterfaceTtlThreshold.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceTtlThreshold
snDvmrpVInterfaceTtlThreshold.description: This is the minimum time-to-live value to forward the packets out of this virtual interface.

snDvmrpVInterfaceAdvertiseLocal.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceAdvertiseLocal
snDvmrpVInterfaceAdvertiseLocal.description: Enable or disable the advertising of this local route.

snDvmrpVInterfaceEncapsulation.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceEncapsulation
snDvmrpVInterfaceEncapsulation.description: Enable or disable the encapsulation of the DVMRP control packets when using IPINIP encapsulation.

snDvmrpVInterfaceStatus.name: snDvmrpVInterfaceStatus
snDvmrpVInterfaceStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: invalid(1)...Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. valid(2)....Setting it to 'valid' has the effect of changing the row to operative.

snDvmrpNeighborTable.name: snDvmrpNeighborTable
snDvmrpNeighborTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's DVMRP neighbors, as discovered by receiving Neighbor Probe messages. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this table is read.

snDvmrpNeighborEntry.name: snDvmrpNeighborEntry
snDvmrpNeighborEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the snDvmrpNeighborTable.

snDvmrpNeighborVifIndex.name: snDvmrpNeighborVifIndex
snDvmrpNeighborVifIndex.description: The value of VifIndex for the virtual interface used to reach this DVMRP neighbor.

snDvmrpNeighborAddress.name: snDvmrpNeighborAddress
snDvmrpNeighborAddress.description: The IP address of the DVMRP neighbor for which this entry contains information.

snDvmrpNeighborUpTime.name: snDvmrpNeighborUpTime
snDvmrpNeighborUpTime.description: The time since this DVMRP neighbor (last) became a neighbor of the local router.

snDvmrpNeighborExpiryTime.name: snDvmrpNeighborExpiryTime
snDvmrpNeighborExpiryTime.description: The minimum time remaining before this DVMRP neighbor will be aged out.

snDvmrpNeighborMajorVersion.name: snDvmrpNeighborMajorVersion
snDvmrpNeighborMajorVersion.description: The neighboring router's major DVMRP version number.

snDvmrpNeighborMinorVersion.name: snDvmrpNeighborMinorVersion
snDvmrpNeighborMinorVersion.description: The neighboring router's minor DVMRP version number.

snDvmrpNeighborCapabilities.name: snDvmrpNeighborCapabilities
snDvmrpNeighborCapabilities.description: This object describes the neighboring router's capabilities. The following shows the position of each bit: bit position meaning ----------- ------ 3 mtrace bit 2 generationID bit 1 prune bit 0 leaf bit The leaf bit indicates that the neighbor has only one interface with neighbors. The prune bit indicates that the neighbor supports pruning. The generationID bit indicates that the neighbor sends its generationID in Probe messages. The mtrace bit indicates that the neighbor can handle mtrace requests.

snDvmrpRouteTable.name: snDvmrpRouteTable
snDvmrpRouteTable.description: The routing table used by DVMRP in place of the unicast routing table. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this table is read.

snDvmrpRouteEntry.name: snDvmrpRouteEntry
snDvmrpRouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information used by DVMRP in place of the unicast routing information.

snDvmrpRouteSource.name: snDvmrpRouteSource
snDvmrpRouteSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of snDvmrpRouteSourceMask identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

snDvmrpRouteSourceMask.name: snDvmrpRouteSourceMask
snDvmrpRouteSourceMask.description: The network mask which when combined with the corresponding value of snDvmrpRouteSource identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

snDvmrpRouteUpstreamNeighbor.name: snDvmrpRouteUpstreamNeighbor
snDvmrpRouteUpstreamNeighbor.description: The address of the upstream neighbor (e.g., RPF neighbor) from which IP datagrams from these sources are received.

snDvmrpRouteVifIndex.name: snDvmrpRouteVifIndex
snDvmrpRouteVifIndex.description: The value of snDvmrpVInterfaceVifIndex for the virtual interface on which IP datagrams sent by these sources are received.

snDvmrpRouteMetric.name: snDvmrpRouteMetric
snDvmrpRouteMetric.description: The distance in hops to the source subnet.

snDvmrpRouteExpiryTime.name: snDvmrpRouteExpiryTime
snDvmrpRouteExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out.

snDvmrpRouteNextHopTable.name: snDvmrpRouteNextHopTable
snDvmrpRouteNextHopTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on the next hops on outgoing interfaces for routing IP multicast datagrams. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this table is read.

snDvmrpRouteNextHopEntry.name: snDvmrpRouteNextHopEntry
snDvmrpRouteNextHopEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the list of next hops on outgoing interfaces to which IP multicast datagrams from particular sources are routed.

snDvmrpRouteNextHopSource.name: snDvmrpRouteNextHopSource
snDvmrpRouteNextHopSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of snDvmrpRouteNextHopSourceMask identifies the sources for which this entry specifies a next hop on an outgoing interface.

snDvmrpRouteNextHopSourceMask.name: snDvmrpRouteNextHopSourceMask
snDvmrpRouteNextHopSourceMask.description: The network mask which when combined with the corresponding value of snDvmrpRouteNextHopSource identifies the sources for which this entry specifies a next hop on an outgoing interface.

snDvmrpRouteNextHopVifIndex.name: snDvmrpRouteNextHopVifIndex
snDvmrpRouteNextHopVifIndex.description: The snDvmrpVInterfaceVifIndex value of the virtual interface for the outgoing interface for this next hop.

snDvmrpRouteNextHopType.name: snDvmrpRouteNextHopType
snDvmrpRouteNextHopType.description: Type is leaf if no neighbors exist on the outgoing virtual interface. Otherwise, type is branch.

snDvmrpVIfStatTable.name: snDvmrpVIfStatTable
snDvmrpVIfStatTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's DVMRP virtual interface statistical counters. snDvmrpEnable must be 'enabled' before this table is read.

snDvmrpVIfStatEntry.name: snDvmrpVIfStatEntry
snDvmrpVIfStatEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the snDvmrpVIfStatTable.

snDvmrpVIfStatVifIndex.name: snDvmrpVIfStatVifIndex
snDvmrpVIfStatVifIndex.description: The ifIndex value of this DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatInPkts.description: The number of packets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatOutPkts.description: The number of packets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInOctets.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInOctets
snDvmrpVIfStatInOctets.description: The number of octets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutOctets.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutOctets
snDvmrpVIfStatOutOctets.description: The number of octets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInProbePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInProbePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatInProbePkts.description: The number of probe packets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutProbePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutProbePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatOutProbePkts.description: The number of probe packets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardProbePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardProbePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardProbePkts.description: The number of probe packets that have been discarded by the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInRtUpdatePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInRtUpdatePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatInRtUpdatePkts.description: The number of route update packets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutRtUpdatePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutRtUpdatePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatOutRtUpdatePkts.description: The number of route update packets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardRtUpdatePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardRtUpdatePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardRtUpdatePkts.description: The number of route update packets that have been discarded by the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInGraftPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInGraftPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatInGraftPkts.description: The number of graft packets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutGraftPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutGraftPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatOutGraftPkts.description: The number of graft packets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardGraftPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardGraftPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardGraftPkts.description: The number of graft packets that have been discarded by the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInGraftAckPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInGraftAckPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatInGraftAckPkts.description: The number of graft acknowledge packets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutGraftAckPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutGraftAckPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatOutGraftAckPkts.description: The number of graft acknowledge packets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardGraftAckPkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardGraftAckPkts
snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardGraftAckPkts.description: The number of graft acknowledge packets that have been discarded by the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatInPrunePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatInPrunePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatInPrunePkts.description: The number of prune packets that have arrived on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatOutPrunePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatOutPrunePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatOutPrunePkts.description: The number of prune packets that have been sent on the DVMRP virtual interface.

snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardPrunePkts.name: snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardPrunePkts
snDvmrpVIfStatDiscardPrunePkts.description: The number of prune packets that have been discarded by the DVMRP virtual interface.

snFsrpGroupOperMode.name: snFsrpGroupOperMode
snFsrpGroupOperMode.description: The FSRP is configured on this system either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. disabled(0)..........disable FSRP enabled(1)...........activate FSRP

snFsrpIfStateChangeTrap.name: snFsrpIfStateChangeTrap
snFsrpIfStateChangeTrap.description: Indicates whether the SNMP agent process is permitted to generate FSRP interface state change traps.

snFsrpIfTable.name: snFsrpIfTable
snFsrpIfTable.description: The FSRP Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of FSRP.

snFsrpIfEntry.name: snFsrpIfEntry
snFsrpIfEntry.description: The FSRP Interface Entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of FSRP.

snFsrpIfPort.name: snFsrpIfPort
snFsrpIfPort.description: The physical router port of this FSRP interface.

snFsrpIfIpAddress.name: snFsrpIfIpAddress
snFsrpIfIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the physical router port of this interface.

snFsrpIfVirRtrIpAddr.name: snFsrpIfVirRtrIpAddr
snFsrpIfVirRtrIpAddr.description: The IP Address of the Virtual Router for the interface. The Virtual Router IP address need to be configured on the interface before Redundant Router Function can operate on the interface. This address has to be same on all the routers that going to participate in the Redundant Router Function on a given subnet.

snFsrpIfOtherRtrIpAddr.name: snFsrpIfOtherRtrIpAddr
snFsrpIfOtherRtrIpAddr.description: The IP Address of the Other Router on this ip subnet that operates FSRP and to whom the Keep Alive message need to be sent by this router. This object must be configured for FSRP to work correctly

snFsrpIfPreferLevel.name: snFsrpIfPreferLevel
snFsrpIfPreferLevel.description: The higher the number the higher the priority is. This parameter decides which router should becomes the Active Router for the interface. A Router with higher priority selected to becomes the Active Router.

snFsrpIfTrackPortMask.name: snFsrpIfTrackPortMask
snFsrpIfTrackPortMask.description: This object specifies the identity of the physical port whose state is to be monitored. Each bit is a port of the system. Default value is 0. If this object is configured then the Preference Level of this interface will be adjusted dynamically depending on the state of the Track Port. The interface's Preference Level is reduced by value of Preference Level parameter when the Track Port states first changes from UP to DOWN. When the Track Port next comes up the interface's Preference Level is increased by the amount specified by the Preference Level. The Standalone router FSRP Track port membership (Not used for Chassis Product)

snFsrpIfRowStatus.name: snFsrpIfRowStatus
snFsrpIfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. snFsrpIfState.name: snFsrpIfState
